{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["SOLAR PHYSICS"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "distributionDate": "2019-07-12T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "fundingNumbers": [{"number": "NSG-7161", "type": "CONTRACT_GRANT"}], "title": "Second-phase acceleration versus second-step acceleration in solar flares", "stiType": "CONFERENCE_PROCEEDINGS", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-11T15:34:00.0000000+00:00", "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19830038816, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Bai, T."}, "organization": {"name": "California, University", "location": "La Jolla, CA, United States"}}, "id": "b8c640d03a394ed28665913c5f29e95b"}], "stiTypeDetails": "Conference Proceedings", "technicalReviewType": "TECHNICAL_REVIEW_TYPE_NONE", "modified": "2011-08-17T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "id": 19830038816, "created": "2013-08-11T15:34:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "Solar hard-X-ray and gamma-ray observations are reviewed that make it possible to distinguish two phases and two steps of energetic electron and ion acceleration in solar flares. A distinction is made between second-phase and second-step acceleration of electrons, protons, and heavy nuclei in flares, and the impulsive acceleration of flare protons is discussed. Hard-X-ray and gamma-ray time profiles of a solar flare are examined in detail. It is proposed that in flares producing impulsive gamma rays, energetic protons and heavy nuclei are accelerated by the second-step mechanism.", "isLessonsLearned": false, "disseminated": "METADATA_ONLY", "meetings": [{"submissionId": 19830038816, "endDate": "1981-08-08T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "sponsors": [{"meta": {"organization": {"name": "U. S. Department of Energy"}}, "meetingId": "